<div class="body-page directoryopus-link-body">
	<h1 class="directoryopus-link-heading"><img class="directoryopus-logo" src="/plugins/discourse-directoryopus/images/opus_logo.png" alt=""> {{i18n "directoryopus.linkopus_heading"}}</h1>

	<hr>

	<h2>You Are Not Logged In</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>If you have not created a forum account, please {{d-button action="showCreateAccount" class="btn-primary btn-small sign-up-button" label="sign_up"}}, then return here.</li>
		<li>If you have a forum account, please {{d-button action="showLogin" class="btn-primary btn-small login-button" icon="user" label="log_in"}}.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Returning Here</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<div>You can return here via <b>Account Linking</b> in the top-right menu:</div>
			<div><img src="/plugins/discourse-directoryopus/images/opus_account_link_menu.png" width="334" height="181" alt="[Menu Screenshot]"></div>
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Forum Accounts</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>You need a free forum account to post (but not to read, search or download).</li>
		<li>If you're evaluating Opus, you are welcome to make a forum account and ask questions.</li>
		<li>If you own an Opus licence, you can link it to your forum account.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>What Account Linking Does</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Linking your Opus licence to your forum account tells us your posts come from a paying customer.</li>
		<li>We'll be more likely to give detailed answers and implement your suggestions.</li>
		<li>We'll know the Opus version you're on (e.g. Opus 12 Pro). The helps us answer your questions.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>What Account Linking Does Not Do</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Simple questions may still be answered before ones requiring research, no matter who each comes from.</li>
		<li>Linking gives your requests a boost but does not guarantee when or if they will be implemented.</li>
		<li>If you are excessively, unapologetically rude or disruptive then we may still limit your forum account.</li>
	</ul>
</div>
